       reply:["guest","Sterling Crane","[the grin flickers] ...Why HERE. [a beat] Good question, and you asked it before I could redirect, which is annoying. Honest answer? The platforms have handlers. Producers, sponsors, lawyers who pre-screen my talking points. Here there's nobody between my mouth and your microphone, which is either the most liberating or the most dangerous thing I've done in years. I brought something tonight I've never shown on a real platform. Something that'd end the act or confirm it, and I'm not sure which is worse. [recovers the grin] But we'll get to that ORGANICALLY, as I said. First, the headline."],
       reveal:"He's here because a pirate frequency has no handlers — he brought something he can't show on real platforms",
